The head of Isfahan’s judiciary said authorities have ordered the identification and seizure of assets belonging to 100 people accused of supporting Iran’s enemies.

Asadollah Jafari said the individuals were, in his words, “traitors to the homeland” who had supported enemy actions against Iran in different ways.
